  <summary date="2021-06-15T13:59:30Z" status="Introduced in House">Delivering Envelopes Judiciously On-time Year-round Act or the DEJOY Act

This bill requires the U.S. Postal Service (USPS) to maintain the service standards for first-class mail that were in effect on January 1, 2021. The Postmaster General proposed in March 2021 a 10-year restructuring plan for the USPS that would lengthen the permissible mail-delivery window.</summary>
